## Component Rules

### `'use client'` — Only Where Required
Add `'use client'` only for: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, `IntersectionObserver`, event listeners. Everything else is a Server Component.

### Asset Paths
Always leading slash: `/assets/abp/imgs/crossstreet.png`. Never dynamic string composition.

### Images
Use `next/image` for all images. Hero brand mark gets `priority` (LCP candidate). All others lazy by default.

### Per-Component Key Requirements

| Component | Requirement |
|---|---|
| `EditorialLine` | 1px divider, `var(--color-divider)`, brightens to `--color-primary` on adjacent hover |
| `IndexRow` | Hover: `translateX(1rem)` + adjacent EditorialLine brightens |
| `MediaFeature` | `saturate(0.85)` default; hover `saturate(1) scale(1.03)` — on wrapper div only |
| `OffsetGrid` | Right col `margin-top: 4rem` desktop; collapses to single col at `max-width: 768px` |
| `StoryCard` | No fixed width/height; glassmorphism via `var(--color-card-surface)` + `backdrop-filter: blur(4px)` |
| `Donations` | QR codes side-by-side, centered, no fixed widths |
| `Hero` | Entrance fade-up once on mount; `h1` in `--font-display`; manifesto `max-width: 45ch` |
| `Footer` | `EditorialLine` top border; wordmark in `--font-display`; `SocialButton` for FB + IG |
| `ui/SocialButton` | Circular; `aria-label` required; `rel="noopener noreferrer"` |

### Motion Rules
- Transitions on `transform` and `opacity`/`color`/`background` only — never `width`, `height`, `top`
- Duration: `0.25s ease` for hover; `0.4s ease` for reveal
- No bounce or elastic easing
- Stagger: `transition-delay: calc(var(--i, 0) * 0.08s)`
- `prefers-reduced-motion` is mandatory:

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .reveal { opacity: 1; transform: none; transition: none; }
}
```

### Scroll Reveal (IntersectionObserver)
```tsx
'use client';
const ref = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
useEffect(() => {
  const el = ref.current; if (!el) return;
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    ([entry]) => { if (entry.isIntersecting) el.classList.add('visible'); },
    { threshold: 0.1 }
  );
  observer.observe(el);
  return () => observer.disconnect();
}, []);
```

